The paper proposes an approach that utilizes deep convolutional and recurrent architectures for interpreting fetal echocardiography videos. This involves detecting anatomical structures on spatial region proposals and aggregating this information temporally to quantify progressive motion patterns. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep learning architectures for interpretation suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of video sequences and motion patterns suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of recurrent architectures suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
